# Security Rules

- Never commit secrets, tokens, or private keys.
- Never add DEV auth bypass behavior outside local/test.
- Never log raw auth codes, tokens, passwords, or Authorization headers in production paths.
- Use input validation for every external boundary.
- Keep rate limits enabled for auth endpoints.
- If a secret was exposed, rotate it immediately and move it into the proper secret channel.